\section{Version control with git}

\begin{note}
\lstinline{git} is a \emph{version control system}.
It lets us track different versions of our files,
and ``travel back in time'' to old versions if we need to.
\lstinline{git} is especially useful for facilitating collaboration between mnay humans (or AIs).
A good understanding of \lstinline{git} is necessary for getting a good industry job.
\end{note}

\begin{note}
You will not be able to undestand the problems in this section of the quiz if you have not mastered the git tutorial at \url{https://github.com/mikeizbicki/pullrequest-tutorial/}.
\end{note}
